.include {docs}
.doclang {en}

BakingRL is a desktop host for Rocket League telemetry overlays. It connects to
the local telemetry stream, normalizes match events, loads plugin packages, and
renders plugin-powered visuals in Tauri windows and OBS browser sources.

The core idea is simple: the host is responsible for trust, lifecycle, and
runtime integration; plugins are responsible for presentation, small services,
connectors, and reusable page content.

## Start Here

- [Overview](pages/overview.qd): what BakingRL is and what problem it solves.
- [Setup](pages/setup.qd): local development requirements and run commands.
- [Architecture](pages/architecture.qd): host process, frontend, runtime, and
  data flow.
- [Plugin System](pages/plugin-system.qd): the central model behind packages,
  exports, permissions, and host APIs.
- [Plugin Lifecycle](pages/plugin-lifecycle.qd): install, validate, enable,
  load, mount, reload, and uninstall.
- [Plugin Security](pages/plugin-security.qd): why plugin code is not trusted
  and where enforcement happens.

## Repository Split

The project is split across three sibling repositories:

```txt
BakingRL/         Host application
BakingRLSDK/      SDK, generator, helper CLI, plugin-author documentation
BakingRLPlugins/  First-party and experimental plugins
```

Keep them side by side during local development.
